{
  "text": "In Experiment 1 (\"literal\" search), orthographic distractors were expected to increase adolescents' search times just as they do in adults [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Semantic distractors were also expected to increase search times [CITATION_3] , and the impact of semantic distractors was expected to increase with age, due to a more automatic activation of words' semantic features during search [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
